{% extends "smt_base.html" %}

{% block content %}
<div id="description">
  <p>The current candidiate list, in the format of a .csv file, can be downloaded <a href="{{MEDIA_URL}}trigger/pessto.csv"> here </a>.

  <p>This list is updated daily, and includes objects marked as transient candidate in the last 30 days.

  <p>Here are the detailed description of the columns:
    <ul>
      <li>candidateID: SkyMapper candidate name.</li>
      <li>RA: candidate right ascension.</li>
      <li>DEC: candidate declination.</li>
      <li>mag: latest SkyMapper detection calibrated magnitude.</li>
      <li>magerr: err estimate of the latest magnitude.</li>
      <li>mjd: latest SkyMapper detection MJD.</li>
      <li>filt: latest SkyMapper detection filter.</li>
      <li>discMag: earliest available SkyMapper detection magnitude.</li>
      <li>discMJD: earliest available SkyMapper detection MJD.</li>
      <li>discFilt: earliest available SkyMapper detection filter.</li>
      <li>bestType: current transient type in the SkyMapper database. Cand = candidate. The database may be manually updated if a transient is spectroscopically classified.</li>
      <li>noneMag: last non-detection limit before first detection.</li>
      <li>noneMJD: last non-detection limit MJD.</li>
      <li>noneFilt: last non-detection limit filter.</li>
      <li>newThumbURL: link for new image thumbnail.</li>
      <li>refThumbURL: link for reference image thumbnail.</li>
      <li>diffThumbURL: link for difference image thumbnail.</li>
      <li>finderURL: link for a finding chart.</li>
      <li>candidateURL: candidate webpage on the SMT site, includes lightcurve and comment history.</li>
      <li>status: candidate status.</li>
      <li>numDet: number of SkyMapper detections.</li>
      <li>comment: last change in the SkyMapper database, with associated user comment.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

{% endblock %}
